com.strongloop.android.loopback

Class ModelRepository<T extends Model>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.strongloop.android.remoting.Repository<T>
      • com.strongloop.android.loopback.RestRepository<T>
        • com.strongloop.android.loopback.ModelRepository<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccessTokenRepository, UserRepository

    public class ModelRepository<T extends Model>
extends RestRepository<T>
    A local representative of a single model type on the server, encapsulating the name of the model type for easy Model creation, discovery, and management.

        Creates a new Repository, associating it with the named remote class.
        Parameters:
        className - The remote class name.
        nameForRestUrl - The pluralized class name to use in REST transport. Use null for the default value, which is the plural form of className.
        modelClass - The Model class. It must have a public no-argument constructor.
